It appears to be a microbe found at the bottom of Lake Mono in Yosemiste National Park, California, where it lives in an environment that was considered too poisonous for any form of life, as the lake is rich in arsenic.
The creature somehow uses arsenic for its life, and it is this ability that increases the likelihood that a similar life could exist on other planets that do not have the atmosphere as it is on Earth.
According to astrobiologists, if these organisms use arsenic in their metabolism, it will be proven that "there is another, second life form, different from the one we know".
The Space Agency will announce the actual discovery range for tomorrow's press conference.
